>I just noticed that setting the LONG_LIST_JOBS option does *not* force jobs
>to be listed in long format.

I thought I'd found that too, a few betas ago.  LONG_LIST_JOBS is *not*
intended to make jobs default to -l: "alias jobs='jobs -l'" does that.
It affects the format of the notification one receives when a job
terminates or is suspended.

-zefram

